    <h3 class="heading-color font-weight-bold">The Scale of Plastic Pollution in Water Bodies</h3>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p class="heading-color">
            Each year, approximately 8 million metric tons of plastic waste enter the world's oceans, a figure that is projected to increase if current trends continue. Rivers and lakes are also heavily contaminated, often acting as conduits for plastic waste from land to sea. Studies have found plastic debris even in remote and pristine water bodies, indicating the pervasive nature of this pollution.
